                <td bgColor="#0A0634"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Az[/i]
[br]Couple of points:
When breaking spawn and kiting the initial mobs as not to pull adds how do prevent cross over dmg? Meaning dmg taken when you end at the wall of one track and pace back along the path to the opposite side criss-crossing the mob. They typically will hit me and occasionally stun.

How can this be done with dooming? Sure it may work for one or even two mobs but without the -20sv modifier of embracing (level 63 snare) I have a seriously hard time believing you could keep this up. Multiple snare resists are common!

As for aggro kiting with pet vs. root cooking&gt;seems like root cooking allows for better mob control which is necessary for breaking spawns. Just a thought.

ADDENDUM:
Tested this out last night. Was splitting by rooting one, worked. I root cooked to break the spawn and this seemed to work well. 



