                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Halyanth79</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/30/2003&nbsp;: 10:10:03 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> This camp spot is still doable with A druid, and a Monk.  I still get okay xp and the spec drops are really low prolly been there about 3 weeks straight and havent left the zone playing for 8-12 hour sessions and only see 1-2 a day. Nevertheless the cash is decent and the chance for specs makes this a really nice camp, even though you may have to deal with the summoning mobs.  I can also however confirm The Black suited Valiant Squires cannot be snare and Dont summon, The white suited Valiant Spirits can be snared but summon.  The Valorium Sentries however killed 2-3 every 5 cycles dont summon, easy enought with a Druid, Necro, Monk, Have the monk pull have the necro grab agro with FP, kite it around let the druid dot it up, have the druid attempt to snare it let druid get agro, Necro then begins to dot it up, recast CoC on him 1 and you have agro back, meanwhile letting the Monk, necro and druid pet beat it down, SOE is required for the monk and pets to keep up with the mob.<br /><br />Hope this information Helps!<br /><br />Sage Halyanth Bloodseer<br />Gnomish Witch of Seventh Hammer</span></font></td>
