                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/21/2003&nbsp;: 08:42:14 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Sentries are the only thing that makes this camp tolerable. Besides the fact that they have the higher Spectral drop rate, they are the only thing that presents a challenge.<br /><br />As far as necros having problems with them, I have dotted them to death and I have nuked them to death with ToM. Dotting means I end the fight near full mana (thank you Seduction of Saryn) and nuking means I run around a lot at zero mana waiting to get enough to nuke again. I currently use a 15% spell haste item to get dots off.<br /><br />I have even done a sentry with 2 adds; just kite them all and keep boner off of them. The last thing you want is for him to steal aggro from an add and split them on you. You could pull the U-turn and run straight into a mob.<br /><br />The only way I would root rot guardians was if I was too cheap/broke/stubborn to buy a horse/lizard for aggro kiting. Without a mount, I could see root rotting being better for mana regen, though a lot of that would be offset by the need of an extra spell going at all times.<br /><br />Sow potions/jboots are almost a must for Sentries. It might be possible to do without, but why? The drops here easily offset potion fees.<br /><br />My lizard is green and he plays the drums.<br /><br />Lich Sabahk Anpu<br />65 Iksar Necromancer<br />Fennin Ro Server<br />La Familia Guild<br /><br /><br /><img src="http://www3.mb.sympatico.ca/~edenwpg/sabahk/dsig.jpg" border="0"><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490206" target="_blank"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490206" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490206</a></a></span></font></td>
